Happy Birthday to #AnnieMorris, born on this day in 1978.

Encompassing sculpture, tapestry, painting and drawing, Morris’s vibrant and colourful art draws the viewer into her narrative world. Like the interpretations of the female body seen in the work of Louise Bourgeois, Morris's sculptures emerged as a metaphor for the pregnant female form and its fragility. Yet they evolved into an expression of joy and balance over time, with a positive vibrance in Morris's wobbling sculpted balls and deep, bright shades of ultramarine, violet and viridian green, a palette Morris has perfected in the last five years.

Morris currently has a sculpture on auction for the nonprofit charity Cure3 Exhibition in support of research for Parkinson's Disease at Bonhams, London. The auction is on until tomorrow, 17 January.

Next Up: Opening in February 2023, ‘Two Worlds Entwined: Annie Morris and Idris Khan’ will explore the artistic practices of Annie Morris and Idris Khan within the historic and intimate setting of Newlands House gallery.

