Daniel Crews-Chubb releases his first limited-edition print with Avant Arte, 𝙄𝙢𝙢𝙤𝙧𝙩𝙖𝙡 𝙄𝙄 (𝙩𝙪𝙧𝙦𝙪𝙤𝙞𝙨𝙚) next Thursday.

The print is a continuation of Crews-Chubb's 'Immortals' series, exploring the world of mythological beings who inhabit his vivid paintings and reveling in the tension between the ugly and the sublime. Here, a totemic figure emerges from a frenzy of teal, orange and violet brushstrokes.

Inspired by an original painting, the edition of 35 translates Crews-Chubb’s distinct impasto marks into an archival pigment print. The artist gravitates towards texture in reaction to the modern-day flatness of digital images.

Release Date: 16 February 2023

